    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "Erd\\H{o}s and Hajnal originally conjectured that there are no such $G_1,G_2$, but in fact $G_1=C_4$ and $G_2=C_6$ is an example. Indeed, for this pair Ne\\v{s}et\\v{r}il and R\\\"{o}dl established the first property and Erd\\H{o}s and Hajnal the second (in fact every $C_4$-free graph is a countable union of trees). \n\nWhether this is true for $G_1=K_4$ and $G_2=K_3$ is the content of [595]."
    },
